<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 8500 - ADJUSTMENTS -
        HEADLAMP REPLACEMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="4">
        <title>HEADLAMP REPLACEMENT</title>
        <para>To replace head lamp and directional bulbs, unlatch hood on both sides and tilt hood forward.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the rear side of the headlight housing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn the socket cover and remove.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove light socket pigtail plug.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0900643" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900643.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px" resolution="200"/>
            <caption>Figure 42. Headlight Bulb Access</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. SOCKET COVER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. MOUNTING STUDS</callout1>
                <callout1>3. HEAD LAMP PLUG</callout1>
                <callout1>4. HEADLIGHT HOUSING</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f0900642" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900642.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px" resolution="200"/>
            <caption>Figure 43. Head Lamp Replacement</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. SOCKET COVER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. HEADLIGHT ASSEMBLY MOUNTING STUD WITH NUT</callout1>
                <callout1>3. SOCKET</callout1>
                <callout1>4. HEADLIGHT HOUSING</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Twist bulb retainer and lift up.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove bulb.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0900644" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900644.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px" resolution="200"/>
            <caption>Figure 44. Seal Beam Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. HEADLIGHT ADJUSTMENT SCREW</callout1>
                <callout1>2. HEADLIGHT HARNESS</callout1>
                <callout1>3. HEADLIGHT HOUSING</callout1>
                <callout1>4. SOCKET SEAL</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f0900645" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900645.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px" resolution="200"/>
            <caption>Figure 45. Bulb Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. HEADLIGHT HALOGEN BULB</callout1>
                <callout1>2. HEADLIGHT HOUSING</callout1>
                <callout1>3. ADJUSTMENT SCREW</callout1>
                <callout1>4. HEADLIGHT HARNESS</callout1>
                <callout1>5. HEAD LIGHT PLUG</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
